SECTION 4: THE PROTON ANALOGY
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  The proton: 99% of its mass is the QCD FIELD CONFIGURATION,
  not the quark constituents. The field configuration is a soliton.
  Its mass is determined by Λ_QCD, which comes from b₃ = -7.

  The dwarf spheroidal: ~99% of its mass is the DM SOLITON,
  not the stellar constituents. The soliton is a field configuration.
  Its mass is determined by... what?

    Proton: pattern/total                  0.99
    Draco: dark/total                      0.99462962963

  Both are >99%% pattern energy.
  The proton's pattern scale is set by b₃ = -7 → Λ_QCD ~ 300 MeV.
  What sets the dwarf soliton's scale?

    Dwarf soliton ratio                    186.20689655
    Spiral soliton ratio                   6.0
    Ratio of ratios (dwarf/spiral)         31.034482759
    Median dwarf DM/vis                    100.0
    (Median dwarf) / (cosmic DM/baryon)    18.809220547
    |b2_SM_num| = 19                       19.0
    |b2_SM_num| - 1 = 18                   18.0
  [PASS] Dwarf/cosmic ratio ~ 19 = |b2_SM_num| within 5%
        ratio = 18.81, |b2_SM| = 19, miss = 1.0%

  OBSERVATION: The median dwarf DM/visible ratio divided by
  the cosmic DM/baryon ratio is ~ 19 = |b₂_SM_num|.
  This is the SU(2) beta numerator BEFORE the CD modification.
  The spiral ratio uses 13 (after CD). The dwarf uses 19 (before CD).

  HYPOTHESIS: Dwarfs formed BEFORE the CD threshold was crossed.
  Their soliton structure uses SM betas, not modified betas.
  Spirals formed AFTER. Their structure uses modified betas.

