SECTION 9: BARYON LOADING — THE SPECTRUM EXPLAINED
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  HYPOTHESIS: The soliton mass is FIXED by the field configuration.
  The visible mass is VARIABLE — determined by baryon loading
  (cooling, star formation, feedback).

  DM/visible = M_soliton / M_baryons_loaded

  High DM/vis (dwarfs): small potential well, inefficient cooling,
    strong feedback, few baryons loaded → nearly pure soliton
  Low DM/vis (spirals): deep potential, efficient cooling,
    many baryons loaded → soliton + significant disk

  Baryon loading efficiency (Moster et al. 2013 approximate):

    M_halo(M☉)     f_baryon    DM/baryon
  ------------ ------------ ------------
        1.0e+7        0.001        999.0
        1.0e+8        0.005        199.0
        1.0e+9         0.01         99.0
       1.0e+10         0.03        32.33
       1.0e+11         0.05         19.0
       1.0e+12         0.16         5.25
       1.0e+13          0.1          9.0
       1.0e+14         0.12        7.333

  PATTERN: DM/baryon is highest at low and high halo mass.
  The minimum is at M ~ 10¹² M☉ (Milky Way scale).
  Dwarfs (M ~ 10⁸) have DM/baryon ~ 200 from inefficient loading.
  This is the STANDARD explanation in CDM.
  The soliton picture AGREES — but says the DM is a soliton,
  not a particle halo.

