SECTION 11: SM vs MODIFIED BETA — FORMATION EPOCH
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  From Section 4: median dwarf DM/vis divided by cosmic
  DM/baryon ≈ 19 = |b₂_SM_num| (before CD modification).

  HYPOTHESIS: The soliton structure depends on which beta
  coefficients were active when the soliton formed.

    DM/baryon (SM epoch, 22/19*π)          3.6376335989
    DM/baryon (modified epoch, 22/13*π)    5.3165414138
    Ratio (modified/SM)                    1.4615384615
    19/13                                  1.4615384615
  [PASS] Modified/SM ratio = 19/13
        expected: 19/13 = 1.4615384615
        got:      19/13 = 1.4615384615
        match:    EXACT

  The ratio of the two DM/baryon values is exactly 19/13
  = |b₂_SM_num| / |b₂_mod_num|.
  This is the SAME ratio that appears in the Lambda identity
  57/39 = 19/13 from the beta unification.

  If dwarfs formed in the SM epoch:
    DM/baryon_dwarf = (22/19)π × (baryon loading factor)
  If spirals formed in the modified epoch:
    DM/baryon_spiral = (22/13)π × (baryon loading factor)

  The ratio 19/13 = 1.462 accounts for some of the
  dwarf vs spiral difference, but not the factor of ~20.
  The rest comes from baryon loading efficiency.

